1
00:00:00,300 --> 00:00:03,081
Right now — somewhere in India —

2
00:00:03,081 --> 00:00:06,906
an old man is being told he is under arrest.

3
00:00:06,906 --> 00:00:11,425
A voice says his name is in a money-laundering case.

4
00:00:11,425 --> 00:00:15,076
"Stay on the line. Don't tell your family.

5
00:00:15,076 --> 00:00:18,466
Transfer the money to clear your name."

6
00:00:18,466 --> 00:00:20,813
By the time anyone notices…

7
00:00:20,813 --> 00:00:23,246
his life's savings are gone.

8
00:00:23,246 --> 00:00:26,028
This is the digital-arrest scam.

9
00:00:26,028 --> 00:00:29,157
Last year it stole Rs 19,000 crore —

10
00:00:29,157 --> 00:00:31,330
one phone call at a time.

11
00:00:31,330 --> 00:00:35,415
Every tool built to stop it protects the bank —

12
00:00:35,415 --> 00:00:38,718
not the frightened person on the call.

13
00:00:38,718 --> 00:00:40,978
It warns them on a screen…

14
00:00:40,978 --> 00:00:45,584
but the people losing everything often can't read it.

15
00:00:45,584 --> 00:00:47,236
So we built Kavach.

16
00:00:47,236 --> 00:00:50,539
A shield on the phone he already owns.

17
00:00:50,539 --> 00:00:54,884
No internet. No cloud. Nothing leaves the device —

18
00:00:54,884 --> 00:00:57,579
airplane mode, the entire time.

19
00:00:57,579 --> 00:01:00,882
Kavach never asks "is the voice fake."

20
00:01:00,882 --> 00:01:04,880
It listens for the script every scammer uses —

21
00:01:04,880 --> 00:01:10,269
urgency, secrecy, "send money to a safe account," fake police.

22
00:01:10,269 --> 00:01:12,963
Watch it follow the call. Safe…

23
00:01:12,963 --> 00:01:16,179
then careful, as the pressure builds…

24
00:01:16,179 --> 00:01:18,700
and the moment it is certain—

25
00:01:18,900 --> 00:01:25,000
[  Kavach speaks the warning aloud — in Hindi  ]

26
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:33,200
"Stop. This may be a scam — don't send money
or share any code. Hang up and call family."

27
00:01:33,300 --> 00:01:36,340
It doesn't just flash a red screen.

28
00:01:36,340 --> 00:01:39,902
It speaks. Out loud. In his own language.

29
00:01:39,902 --> 00:01:43,289
For a man who cannot read that warning,

30
00:01:43,289 --> 00:01:46,677
this voice is the hand that says: stop.

31
00:01:46,677 --> 00:01:49,109
And it's real — not a trick.

32
00:01:49,109 --> 00:01:52,584
Tap it, and Kavach shows the exact words

33
00:01:52,584 --> 00:01:54,755
that gave the scam away —

34
00:01:54,755 --> 00:01:58,664
its reasoning, running entirely on the phone.

35
00:01:58,664 --> 00:02:01,096
No servers. No subscription.

36
00:02:01,096 --> 00:02:04,484
Twelve languages, on a Rs 6,000 phone —

37
00:02:04,484 --> 00:02:07,263
for the people who need it most.

38
00:02:07,263 --> 00:02:09,869
Our parents. Our grandparents.

39
00:02:09,869 --> 00:02:13,778
Kavach. It catches the script… not the voice.

40
00:02:13,778 --> 00:02:17,600
And it speaks up — before the money is gone.

